- [ ] Incomplete task

## Code

Inline code such as `write(fd, buffer, count)` should remain distinct without disrupting the line.

```c
#include <stdio.h>

int main(void) {
    puts("hello from C");
    return 0;
}
```

```rust
fn main() {
    let message = String::from("hello from Rust");
    println!("{message}");
}
```

```sh
$ cc hello.c -o hello
$ ./hello
hello from C
```

```text
This deliberately long line should scroll inside its code block instead of making the entire document wider than the viewport: 0123456789abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyzABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ0123456789abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyzABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ
```

## Quotes and separators

> The reader should be able to distinguish a quotation without mistaking it for a decorative card.
>
> A quote may contain more than one paragraph.

